Namibia to Buy $49 Million-Fishing Research Ship From Finland

-- B y   C h a m w e   K a i r a
-- 
2011-05-12T08:22:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/namibia-to-buy-49-million-fishing-research-ship-from-finland.html
Namibia , which exports hake to the
European Union, is buying a fishing research ship from  Finland 
for 340 million Namibian dollars ($49 million), the Ministry of
Fisheries and Marine Resources said in an e-mailed statement.  The government signed a contract for the ship with STX
Finland Oy, according to the statement. The vessel should be
delivered in April 2012.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chamwe Kaira in Windhoek at 
 ckaira@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 